Introduction
Artificial Intelligence (AI) is transforming industries, governments, and societies worldwide. Recent advancements in generative AI, robotics, smart cities, and space exploration are reshaping the global economy. This assignment discusses key developments, emerging technologies such as AGI, industry trends, and legal and ethical considerations.

1. Recent Advancements in Artificial Intelligence
1.1 Generative AI and Foundation Models
Generative AI systems can create text, images, code, and audio. These systems are trained on large datasets and function as foundation models.
Applications include:
    • Content creation
    • Code generation
    • Virtual assistants
    • Research automation
This represents a shift from narrow AI systems to general-purpose intelligent systems.

1.2 Multimodal AI
Multimodal AI processes text, images, audio, and video simultaneously.
Applications:
    • Medical imaging
    • Autonomous vehicles
    • Robotics
    • Smart assistants

1.3 AI in Robotics and Automation
AI enhances automation in:
    • Manufacturing
    • Warehousing
    • Healthcare
    • Transportation
Autonomous systems improve efficiency, reduce human error, and increase productivity.

1.4 AI in Space Exploration
AI is used for:
    • Autonomous spacecraft navigation
    • Satellite image analysis
    • Planetary mapping
    • Rocket landing optimization
AI reduces mission risk and enables deep-space exploration.

2. Artificial General Intelligence (AGI)
Definition
Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) refers to AI systems capable of performing any intellectual task that a human can perform.
Key Characteristics
    • General reasoning
    • Cross-domain learning
    • Adaptability
    • Long-term planning
AGI remains under research and presents both opportunities and safety challenges.

