4. Smart Cities and AI Integration
Definition
A smart city uses AI, IoT, and big data to improve:
    • Traffic management
    • Energy efficiency
    • Waste management
    • Public safety
Applications
    • Smart traffic lights
    • Predictive infrastructure maintenance
    • AI surveillance systems
    • Smart energy grids
Smart cities improve quality of life while optimizing resource usage.

5. Legal and Ethical Issues in AI
5.1 Bias and Fairness
AI systems may reflect bias in training data, leading to discrimination.
5.2 Privacy Concerns
    • Large-scale data collection
    • Facial recognition systems
5.3 Accountability
Responsibility for AI-related harm may fall on developers, companies, or governments.
5.4 Intellectual Property
Ownership of AI-generated content and training data copyright issues remain unresolved.
5.5 AI Safety and Alignment
Ensuring AI systems align with human values is critical to long-term safety.

